comment.body:
The content of the read me is getting kind of out of date.
Some updates could be helpful. E.g. "scratch-resources" header content replacement:
* resources/source: archive of source files for Scratch resources, including the Card Decks, Educator Guides and translations sent to us by translators.
* resources/www: published (PDF) resources on www. All resources are organized by locale - Originals are in the `/en` directory. We only publish PDFs for maximum portability.

comment.diff_hunk:
@@ -0,0 +1,69 @@
+
+version: 2.1
+orbs:
+  aws-s3: circleci/aws-s3@3.0
+  fastly: bankrate/fastly@0.1.0
+executors:
+  default-executor:
+    docker:
+      - image: "cimg/node:lts"
+    working_directory: ~/project
+    resource_class: medium
+
+commands:
+  restore_test_cache:
+    steps:
+      - restore_cache:
+          keys:
+            - v1-deps-{{ .Environment.CIRCLE_JOB }}-{{ .Branch }}-{{ .Revision }}
+            - v1-deps-{{ .Environment.CIRCLE_JOB }}-{{ .Branch }}
+            - v1-deps-
+  save_test_cache:
+    steps:
+      - save_cache:
+          key: v1-deps-{{ .Environment.CIRCLE_JOB }}-{{ .Branch }}-{{ .Revision }}
+          paths:
+            - node_modules
+  setup:
+    steps:
+      - run:
+          name: Setup
+          command: |
+            npm install
+
+jobs:
+  build-and-deploy:
+    executor: default-executor
+    steps:
+      - checkout
+      - setup
+      - aws-s3/sync:
+          arguments: |
+            --acl public-read \
+            --cache-control "maxage=86400, s-maxage=31536000 no-transform"
+          aws-access-key-id: AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID
+          aws-region: AWS_DEFAULT_REGION
+          aws-secret-access-key: AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
+          from: resources
+          to: 's3://scratch-resources'
+      - fastly/purge-all:
+          fastly-key: '${FASTLY_KEY}'
+          service-id: '${FASTLY_SERVICE_ID}'
+  
+workflows:
+  build-and-deploy-workflow:
+    when:
+      or:
+        - equal: [ master, <<pipeline.git.branch>> ]
comment.body: This is a pretty old repo, it would be nice to rename "master" to "main", but I don't know if this is the time to do it.

comment.body:
This comment is out of date now that we flush the cache as part of the deploy. Perhaps it would be better to describe what's happening now for the Scratch Team.

As part of the build process, a script generates the json for scratch-www listing all the resources, and any translated versions by locale. If the repo builds successfully, everything is uploaded to S3, and the fastly cache is flushed to ensure that new versions are served.
